    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender and golden</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the squash is cooking, add your<strong> pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> then add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and give it a good mix up</p><p>Chop <strong>basil </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is cooked, drain and keep in the sieve until later, reserve the pot</p><p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min</p><p>Gradually whisk in the<strong> stock</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a thick sauce remains</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) and stir through until melted \u2013 this is your <strong>white sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta</strong>, <strong>chopped basil </strong>and<strong> roasted squash</strong> <strong>cubes</strong> to the sauce and give it a good mix up</p><p>Transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, snap your <strong>pecan nuts</strong> in half and sprinkle them over</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy pecan & squash pasta bake</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pecan-and-squash-wholewheat-pasta-bake-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Leave the <strong>cheesy pecan & squash pasta bake </strong>to stand for a few min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p><p>Serve with<strong> </strong>the<strong> salad </strong>to the side and drizzle with the <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
